6.  What is string interpolation and concatenation. Write definition with example?

Ans:- String Interpolation and Concatenation in Java

String Interpolation:-
String interpolation in Java allows embedding expressions within string literals. This is achieved using the String.format() method or by using String's format() method directly.

Example:- String name = "Ram";
int age = 23;
String message = """
                Hello, my name is %s 
                and I am %d years old.
                """.formatted(name, age);
System.out.println(message);

Output:- Hello, my name is Ram
and I am 23 years old.



String Concatenation:-
String concatenation in Java refers to the process of combining multiple strings into a single string. This can be achieved using the + operator.

Example:- String firstName = "Aman";
String lastName = "Kesharwani";
String fullName = firstName + " " + lastName;
System.out.println("Full Name: " + fullName);

output:- Full Name: Aman Kesharwani


